</div>
<div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="1">
<div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="1">
<p>Quinquagesimo nono: quis deducet me usque <lb/>
            in Idumaeam? pro quo in Graeco habet: aut quis deducet <lb/>
            <choice><sic>m</sic><corr>in</corr></choice> e? sed superfluum est. <lb n="10"/>
            
</p>
          
</div>
</div>
<div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="1">
<div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="1">
<p>Sexagesimo: <sic>quoniamtu</sic>, <sic>deusmeus</sic>, exaudisti <lb/>
            orationem meam, pro quo legatur in Graeco: quia tu, <lb/>
            deus, exaudisti me. quod non habet in Hebraeo nec in  <lb/>
            <choice><sic>septuagmta</sic><corr>septuaginta</corr></choice> interpretibus et <choice><sic>m</sic><corr>in</corr></choice> Latino additum est.</p></div>

<div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="2"><p>m eodem : <lb/>
            <choice><sic>psallara</sic><corr>psallam</corr></choice> nomini tuo in saeculum saeculi, pro quo <lb n="15"/>
            in Graeco sit: in <choice><sic>saecuum</sic><corr>saeculum</corr></choice>. et in Hebraeo semel habet <sic n="poss">4laed</sic>', id ^ <lb/>
            est 'in aeternum', et non '<sic>lolam</sic>', quod est 'in saeculum'. 
</p>
          
</div>
</div>
<div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="1">
<div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="1">
<p>Sexagesimo primo: quia deus adiutor noster <lb/>
            in aeternum. pro quo in Graeco est: deus adiutor <lb/>
            noster. ergo 'in aeternum' obelus est. <lb n="20"/>
            
</p>
          
</div>
</div>
<div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" n="1">
<div type="textpart" subtype="section" n="1">
